Todo loads State via the caller-provided fileio.Session, scans the filesystem, reconciles specs and markers, builds a CoreAlgorithmContext with TodoAction (propagating baseline Edges), runs the core algorithm to derive closures, and returns the EvaluatedState without saving. The scan's discovered spec-spec Edges are passed via the Scan struct so the core can detect edge add/remove/broken events inside closures. See principles.friction — review without side effects.